-- Dell Expects 20 Percent Growth This Quarter, Plans New Tablet
-- B y   A a r o n   R i c a d e l a
-- 2010-09-22T16:50:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/dell-expects-20-percent-growth-this-quarter-plans-new-tablet.html
Dell Inc. expects about 20 percent
sales growth in the current quarter and plans to release a new
tablet-style computer, Chief Executive Officer Michael Dell said
today.  Dell, on stage at a conference sponsored by Oracle Corp.,
touted a tablet computer running the Android operating system
backed by Google Inc. The machine also sports a 7-inch screen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Ricadela in San Francisco at 
